  "title": "Training Officer Aide / Caring Aide",
  "description": "<p>1. Assess and evaluate the skill levels of clients</p>\n<p>2. Develop and execute clients’ Individual care Plans (ICPs)</p>\n<p>3. Execute and monitor the progress of clients according to their ICPs</p>\n<p>4. Manage classroom and implement behavioural intervention plans</p>\n<p>5. Execute community-referenced outing trips</p>\n<p>6. Execute events and activities for clients</p>\n<p>7. Maintain clients’ attendance and administrative records</p>\n<p>8. Plan, develop and supervise clients’ daily activities and lesson plans</p>\n<p>9. Develop task analyses and responsible for data collection of clients’ progress and managing of behaviours</p>\n<p>10. Provide progress and incident reports</p>\n<p>11. Ensure clients’ health and safety at all times</p>\n<p>12. Ensure classroom orderliness in areas of physical structure and setting up of work stations during class</p>\n<p>13. Assist clients in areas of self-care, grooming and toileting</p>\n<p>14. Collaborate with colleagues from other disciplines and external parties in implementation and development of</p>\n<p>programmes</p>\n<p>15. Collaborate with parents, family members and caregivers to support clients’ overall growth and development</p>\n<p>programmes</p>\n<p>16. Participate in home visits to discuss clients’ interventions and other related matters Any other tasks as assigned.Assess and evaluate</p>\n<p>17. Diploma in occupational therapy, special education, disability studies, early childhood education, psychology,</p>\n<p>general education.</p>\n<p>• Client and family centric</p>\n<p>• High levels of patience and passion for working with adults with disabilities</p>\n<p>* Candidate with lower qualification may be considerd for the post of coach aide and will be trained to be coach after few years of training and experiences</p>\n<p>Working location: Upper Thomson</p>",
